Billy Joel and I have three things in common.   1. We play the piano 2. We write songs 3. We can't read music  This is more common than you might think.  When I write my lyrics I like to include the chord names, but this is a slow and laborious task if you don't have a clue what the chord names are.  This app has come to my rescue.  I bought it just for the reverse look up,  but in time I will probably discover other hidden gems.    If I knew how to reach Billy Joel I'd tell him about this. If any of you know him make sure you mention it,  will ya?

Thankyou for the slash chord support.  Shame you can't enter slash chords in the staff view. Also, it seems odd that only a small portion of the keyboard is shown in "Chords" view (only 1.5 octaves can be scrolled), yet many octaves are shown in the "Reverse Chords"view (5 octaves can read scrolled). This seems like a bug. Galaxy S3.   Also, there's heaps of space on the screen, you should be able to display the inversion AND the slash chord at the same time in "Chords" view without having to switch in menu

This app does everything I need with a fast and clean interface. Displays chords from root key, scales and a little midi keyboard / recorder with multiple sounds. Compositions can be shared via email or you can browse to "/sdcard/minipiano/" so your musical doodles aren't wasted!
